    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "1-3 days of nonspecific\nURI\nsymptoms, followed by 3-4 days of \"barking\"\ncough\n, hoarse voice,\nstridor\n, and\nacute dyspnea\nUsually most severe on days 3-4\nLow-grade\nfever\nRarely drooling or dysphagia; consider alternate etiology if present",
      "subsections": {
        "Mild": {
          "text": "85% of cases\nIntermittent barking\ncough\nStridor\nwith agitation\nMild\ntachypnea\nMild\ntachycardia",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Moderate": {
          "text": "Fussy but alert, interactive, consolable by parents\nStridor\nat rest\nWorsening stridor with agitation\nIncreased\nwork of breathing",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Severe": {
          "text": "Hypoxia\nTachypnea and marked retractions\nAltered mental status\nLess than 1% of cases",
          "tables": []
